natural solution: 6\cdot 11 = 66 &\equiv 1\pmod{13} \end{align} Thus the modulo $13$ inverses of $1,2,3,4,5,6$ are $1,7,9,10,8,11,$ respectively. The only residue from $7$ through $12$ that is not the inverse of a residue from $1$ through $6$ is $\boxed{12}$ (which is its own inverse).
